GOHTTPSERVE
===========

A super simple HTTP server written in Go. Similar to running python3 -m http.server.

Build
=====
To build GOHTTPSERVE, make sure you have Go installed on your system. Then run the following command:
go build serve.go

The compiled binary will be named `serve`.

Run
===
Run it like you would any other binary:
./serve <directory>

For example:

+ Your current working directory: ./serve .
+ Your home directory: ./serve ~
